        <body>       
                                

                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>D. H. Wittenberg.<lb/>
                29 Norfolk St.<lb/>
                N. Y. C.<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. Dr. S. Morais<lb/>
                546 N. 5th St.<lb/>
                Philadelphia<lb/>
                Pa.<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>22 Norfolk St.<lb/></p>
            <p>New York Aug 6<hi rend="sup">th</hi>&#47;95.<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. Dr. S. Morais<lb/></p>
            <p>Revered and dear Teacher&#58;&#45;<lb/></p>
            <p>Last Sabbath I preached<lb/> in New Haven.  As far as I can<lb/> understand&#44; my effort was success&#45;<lb/>ful.  The congregation however is<lb/> so poor&#44; that I have great doubts<lb/> about their being able to engage<lb/> a minister.<lb/></p>
            <p>They intend to call a meeting<lb/> in about two weeks and decide<lb/> this question&#44; should it be de&#45;<lb/>cided in the <sic>affirmitive</sic>&#44; I am<lb/> almost sure to be chosen.<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>While writing this&#44; I received an<lb/> invitation from the congregation<lb/> Beth El.  Buffalo&#44; strict orthodox&#44;<lb/> to preach there next Sabbath.<lb/></p>
            <p>I intend to speak however the<lb/> Sabbath after that.  So I wrote them.<lb/></p>
            <p>Hoping this will receive your<lb/> kind approval.<lb/>  I remain your pupil<lb/> David H. Wittenberg<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
